    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "The purpose of the Initiation Plan Document is for the UNDP efforts in response to the COVID-19 and to  quickly get off the ground an urgent intervention to provide a temporary basic income for marginalized  and excluded women in Nepal in collaboration with the local government and conduct the feasibility  study on basic income for women in Nepal. The project contributes to the UN Nepal Framework for  Responding to the Socio-Economic Impacts of COVID. The initiatives undertaken under this project are  expected to inform and support the design of a full-fledged dedicated project reflecting the priorities  determined by the Feasibility Analysis, the priorities of the Government of Nepal, and the lesson learned  from the pilot initiative conducted in selected municipalities. The initiative is expected to provide  support to marginalized and excluded women in Nepal to cope with immediate survival needs and  support to become more economically empowered, informed and resilient to face the evolving COVID  context. The plan will be implemented by UNDP for 18 months.  Agreed"
      },
